description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen within Midlands Partnership NHS Foundation Trust for an enthusiastic, highly motivated individual with excellent interpersonal skills to support the Directorate of Facilities and Estates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post 3 - Professional Waste Lead Trust Wide.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsible for the day to day management of across the North division for the Facilities administration teams, Housekeeping, Portering and waste management contracted services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting to the Facilities Senior Performance and Quality Manager, the post holder’s main duties will include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To lead on Portering services both operationally and professionally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To lead on Trust wide Waste requirements and to keep the trust updated on new technology, innovations and waste legislation (to include General/offensive and Clinical waste, aligning service provision and procedures across all sites and manage contracts within financial budget).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regular service /staff updates to be delivered, ensuring that full understanding of the contract KPIs,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Developing Environmental waste policy/SOP&#96;s, procedure practices to promote environmentally sensitive services and accreditation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suggest and implement new improved ways of working in all areas of the department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Engage and support the Sustainable development plan for Waste.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience in a similar Facilities Management operational role or a Waste Manager post would be an advantage, as would previous NHS experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should meet all the essential aspects of the Person Specification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Further Information:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details about this role please contact Mark Cooper, Head of Facilities on telephone number: 0300 790 7000 or Email: Mark.cooper@mpft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
